      },
      "lineNbr": 3,
      "author": {
        "id": 1072905
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-15T07:58:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This implementation targets Ollama’s _OpenAI-compatible_ API (`/v1/...`) [[1]](https://ollama.com/blog/openai-compatibility) rather than Ollama’s *native* API (`/api/...`) [[2]](https://docs.ollama.com/api/introduction). I think is fine, especially since it allows the provider to work with other OpenAI-compatible Llama servers as well.\n\nHowever, I think the documentation should make this explicit so users do not configure a native Ollama endpoint such as http://localhost:11434/api and expect it to work.\n\nWDYT?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 3,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 3,
        "endChar": 79
      },
      "revId": "40125a816847116494129f4cce93821f76787a8d",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
    },
